    "## Next Steps (Conceptual)\n",
    "\n",
    "The practical progression from this preparatory outline would be:\n",
    "\n",
    "1.  **Dataset Acquisition and Curation:**\n",
    "    - Choose and download a suitable dataset (e.g., a subset of OpenImages, or start collecting custom data).\n",
    "    - Convert annotations to a consistent format (e.g., COCO JSON).\n",
    "\n",
    "2.  **Environment Setup:**\n",
    "    - Ensure a Python environment with PyTorch, torchvision, pycocotools, and other necessary libraries is set up.\n",
    "\n",
    "3.  **Implement Custom Dataset Class:**\n",
    "    - Write the PyTorch `Dataset` class to load your specific image data and annotations.\n",
    "\n",
    "4.  **Develop Training Script:**\n",
    "    - Write the main training script incorporating the model loading/modification, DataLoaders, optimizer, training loop, and evaluation logic.\n",
    "\n",
    "5.  **Initial Training Runs:**\n",
    "    - Start with a small subset of data or few epochs to debug the pipeline.\n",
    "    - Monitor loss curves and validation metrics.\n",
    "\n",
    "6.  **Iterative Refinement:**\n",
    "    - Adjust hyperparameters (learning rate, batch size, augmentation strength).\n",
    "    - Potentially gather more data or refine annotations based on initial results."
